# ============================================================================
# MULTI-AGENT APPROVAL WORKFLOW
# ============================================================================
#
# When you submit a WordPress deployment job:
#
# 1. Infrastructure Validation
#    ✓ Check required tools are available
#    ✓ Verify API keys configured
#    ✓ Validate resources allocated
#    ✓ Estimate token costs
#
# 2. Category Head Selection
#    → System identifies 2 category-head agents
#    → Example for WORDPRESS_CMS:
#      - wordpress_fullstack_theme_builder
#      - wordpress_divi_elementor_agent
#
# 3. Independent Review
#    → Each agent reviews independently
#    → Checks alignment with capabilities
#    → Validates budget and feasibility
#    → Provides confidence score (0-1)
#
# 4. Voting
#    → Each votes: APPROVED, REJECTED, or ABSTAIN
#    → Need 2 APPROVED votes to proceed
#    → Any REJECT blocks deployment
#
# 5. Consensus Reasoning
#    → System generates summary of decision
#    → Includes concerns and recommendations
#    → Provides audit trail
#
# 6. Deployment or Rejection
#    → APPROVED: Job executes
#    → REJECTED: User notified with reasoning
#    → Tracks actual vs estimated token usage
#
# ============================================================================
# GETTING YOUR WORDPRESS CREDENTIALS
# ============================================================================
#
# WordPress.com OAuth (Recommended):
#   1. Go to https://developer.wordpress.com/apps/
#   2. Click "Create New Application"
#   3. Fill in application details:
#      - Name: DevSkyy Agent Platform
#      - Description: Automated WordPress management via AI agents
#      - Website URL: http://localhost:8000
#      - Redirect URLs: http://localhost:8000/api/v1/wordpress/oauth/callback
#   4. Copy Client ID and Client Secret
#   5. Paste into .env file
#
# Self-Hosted WordPress Application Passwords:
#   1. Log into your WordPress admin
#   2. Go to Users → Profile
#   3. Scroll to "Application Passwords"
#   4. Enter application name: "DevSkyy Agents"
#   5. Click "Add New Application Password"
#   6. Copy the generated password
#   7. Paste into .env as SKYY_ROSE_APP_PASSWORD
#
